{"title_page": "Vitamin Connection", "text_new": "{{Infobox video game\n|title           = Vitamin Connection\n|image           = Vitamin_Connection_cover_art.jpg\n|caption         = \n|developer       = [[WayForward]]\n|publisher       = WayForward\n|director        = James Montagna<ref name=\"Interview\"/>\n|designer        = \n|artist          = \n|programmer      = \n|composer        = \n|series          = \n|engine          = \n|released        = February 20, 2020\n|genre           = [[Action game|Action]], [[Adventure game|adventure]]\n|modes           = [[Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n|platforms       = [[Nintendo Switch]]\n}}\n\n'''''Vitamin Connection''''' is an [[video game]] developed and published by [[WayForward]], exclusively for the [[Nintendo Switch]]. It was released on February 20, 2020, to positive critical reception. [[Limited Run Games]] distributed limited physical versions of the title.\n\n==Gameplay==\nPlayers take control of one of two characters, Vita-Boy and Mine-Girl, who use the microscopic Capsule Ship to fight off viruses and other enemies hosting within the Sable family, which makes them ill.<ref name=\"Exclusive2\">{{citeweb| last=|first=|url = https://wayforward.com/vitamin-connection-everything-you-need-to-know/ | title = Vitamin Connection: Everything You Need to Know|work = Wayforward | publisher = Wayforward | date = January 29, 2020 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref> The ship itself is controlled with an individual Joy-Con and motion controls, which are used to control and ship and execute attacks. Main levels are navigated using the tilt controls of the Switch.<ref name=\"Interview\">{{citeweb| last=Lane|first=Gavin|url = http://www.nintendolife.com/news/2020/02/feature_wayforward_on_vitamin_connections_switch_exclusivity_challenges_and_influences | title = Feature: WayForward On Vitamin Connection's Switch Exclusivity, Challenges And Influences|work = Nintendo Life | publisher = NLife Media | date = February 21, 2020 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref> Various \"[[Minigame|sub-games]]\" are also present throughout the adventure.\n\n==Development==\nThe game was announced on August 13, 2019 in a press release by Wayforward.<ref name=\"Announce\">{{citeweb| last=|first=|url = https://wayforward.com/wayforward-announces-vitamin-connection-for-switch/ | title = WayForward Announces Vitamin Connection for Switch|work = Wayforward | publisher = Wayforward | date = August 13, 2019 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref> The title was always intended to be a Switch exclusive, with the team stated they were impressed by the system's hardware upon receiving a development kit and wanted to create a game tailored towards the console's unorthodox capabilities.<ref name=\"Interview\"/><ref name=\"Exclusive2\"/><ref name=\"Exclusive1\">{{citeweb| last=|first=|url = https://gonintendo.com/stories/353829-wayforward-explains-how-they-came-up-with-the-idea-for-vitamin-com | title = WayForward Explains How They Came Up With The idea for Vitamin Connection|work = GoNintendo | publisher = GoNintendo | date = January 30, 2020 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref> Development officially started in 2017, but funding difficulties stalled progression on the title and for a period forced the team to work on other internal projects.<ref name=\"Interview\"/><ref name=\"Funding\">{{citeweb| last=|first=|url = https://gonintendo.com/stories/355488-vitamin-connection-started-development-in-2017-but-funding-held | title = Vitamin Connection Started Development In 2017 But Funding Held the Project Back|work = GoNintendo | publisher = GoNintendo | date = February 21, 2020 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref> The game was heavily inspired by [[Jet Set Radio]] and the [[Katamari]] series, specifically with respect to their focus on a creativity, a distinct artstyle and the emphasis the game's place on their soundtracks.<ref name=\"Interview\"/>\n\n==Release==\n''Vitamin Connection'' got its first trailer in January, 2020, and was announced to have a release date of February 20, 2020 as a downloadable title on the [[Nintendo eShop]].<ref name=\"Trailer\">{{citeweb| last=Wong|first=Alistair|url = https://www.siliconera.com/vitamin-connection-shows-off-its-colorful-pop-aesthetic-co-op-gameplay-in-first-trailer/ | title = Vitamin Connection Shows Off Its Colorful Pop Aesthetic Co-op Gameplay in First Trailer|work = Siliconera | publisher = Enthusiast Gaming | date = January 11, 2020 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref> The game received a limited physical release by [[Limited Run Games]] alongside ''Mighty Switch Force! Collection'', and ''Mystik Belle'' for a \"Wayforward Day.\"<ref name=\"Physical\">{{citeweb| last=|first=|url = https://nintendowire.com/news/2020/01/10/vitamin-connection-mighty-switch-force-collection-getting-physical-releases-at-limited-run-games/ | title = Vitamin Connection, Mighty Switch Force! Collection getting physical releases at Limited Run Games|work = Nintendo Wire | publisher = Nintendo Wire | date = January 10, 2020 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref> Standard editions went up for a two-week pre-order period beginning on January 17, while a collector's edition was limited to 2,000 copies.<ref name=\"Physical\"/><ref name=\"Physical2\">{{citeweb| last=Lopez|first=Azario|url = https://noisypixel.net/vitamin-connection-switch-release-date-physical-edition/ | title = WayForward\u2019s \u2018Vitamin Connection\u2019 Gets Switch Release Date, New Trailer, and Physical Release From Limited Run Games|work = Noisy Pixel | publisher = Noisy Pixel | date = January 10, 2020 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = (NS) 78/100<ref name=\"MCNS\">{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/switch/vitamin-connection|title=Vitamin Connection for Nintendo Switch Reviews - Metacritic|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n|NLife={{rating|7|10}}<ref name=\"NintendoLife\">{{cite web|last=Mundy|first=Jon|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/reviews/switch-eshop/vitamin_connection|title=Vitamin Connection Review (Switch eShop)|publisher=Nintendo Life |date=February 22, 2020 |accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref>}}\n''Vitain Connection'' was generally well received by critics. [[Review aggregator]] website [[Metacritic]] gave the game 78/100, based on 6 reviews.<ref name=\"MCNS\"/>\n\nNintendo World Report gave the game a 9/10, praising its gameplay, content and style, though did offer some criticism towards the backtracking the tames featured.<ref name=\"Review\">{{citeweb| last=Koopman|first=Dan|url = http://www.nintendoworldreport.com/review/52923/vitamin-connection-switch-review | title = Vitamin Connection (Switch) Review|work = Nintendo World Report | publisher = Nintendo World Report | date = February 20, 2020 | accessdate = February 21, 2020}}</ref> Jon Mundy of ''Nintendo Life'' gave the game an overall positive review, praising the visuals, co-op gameplay and the variety that the game offers. However, he mentioned some criticism regarding the controls and the game's frequent use of backtracking.<ref name=\"NintendoLife\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://wayforward.com/ Nintendo's listing for ''Vitamin Connection'']\n* [https://wayforward.com/ Wayforward's website]\n\n[[Category:2020 video games]]\n[[Category:Action game stubs]]\n[[Category:Action video games]]\n[[Category:Adventure games]]\n[[Category:Cooperative video games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer and single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch eShop games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch games]]\n[[Category:Nintendo Switch-only games]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox video game\n|title           = Vitamin Connection\n|image           = Vitamin_Connection_cover_art.jpg\n|caption         = \n|developer       = [[WayForward]]\n|publisher       = WayForward\n|director   